formula: Expansion of 1 + eta(q)*eta(q^11)/(eta(q^3)*eta(q^33)), in powers of q. - _G. C. Greubel_, Jun 19 2018
mathematica: eta[q_]:= q^(1/24)*QPochhammer[q]; A := (eta[q]*eta[q^11])/(eta[q^3] *eta[q^33]); a := CoefficientList[Series[1 + A, {q, 0, 60}], q]; Table[a[[n]], {n, 1, 50}] (* _G. C. Greubel_, Jun 19 2018 *)
